external_knowledge:
- 'Top 3 drivers' refers to the drivers with the highest total points in each season;
- 'Total points' are the sum of points earned by the driver over all races in the season;
- 'Season' is a period during which the racing events take place.

- "champions of the racing world" refers to the drivers with the highest number of wins and poles in a season;
- "stars that have shone the brightest" refers to the top-performing drivers;
- "leading the pack" means ranking first in the performance metrics.

- "shining stars" refers to the top 3 active drivers with the most career wins;
- "within each team" indicates that the ranking is done per team;
- "active drivers" means drivers who are currently active (`active = 1`).

- "shone the brightest" refers to the drivers with the highest number of wins, poles, and stage wins;
- "racing circuit" refers to the context of car racing;
- "this season" indicates the current racing season.

- "2022 NASCAR Cup Series" is a specific season in the NASCAR racing calendar;
- "Stage wins" refer to the number of times a driver finished in the first position at the end of each stage in a race;
- "Finish position" is the final position of a driver at the end of the race;
- "Total laps completed" is the sum of all laps completed by the drivers at a particular track during the season.

- "Top 5 drivers" refers to the drivers with the lowest average finish positions and the highest total laps completed;
- "Average finish position" is calculated by averaging the finish positions of a driver across all races in a season;
- "Total laps completed" is the sum of all laps completed by a driver in a season.

sql:
SELECT driver_name
FROM drivers
WHERE career_wins = (SELECT MAX(career_wins) FROM drivers);

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM drivers
WHERE career_wins > (SELECT AVG(career_wins) FROM drivers);
